  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Linking small holder farmers to markets in Midlands Province - Phase 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Phase 2 focus will be to, firstly, provide further support to women who own or lead businesses and secondly, help small businesses to involve their families in decision-making. In this, we will apply the GALS methodology, to change household power dynamics over time. We plan to test the hypothesis that there is a commercial benefit from women in leadership and management roles. Women are the primary source of labour in agriculture and there is some evidence that they may influence adherence to contracts, and adoption of improved agronomic practices and post-harvest handling.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective is to enable 3,000 smallholder farmers to have access to a new market as a result of EXTRA intervention.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will work at provincial level to find markets for the CORE value chains that promote smallholder farmer access to affordable input and profitable output markets.</narrative>
  </description>
